records.addlTxt:
The State moves to delete the enhancer in count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of possess THC in count 1.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of disorderly conduct in count 3.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, possess drug paraphernalia.  Motion granted.
On count 1, possess THC, Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) maintain fulltime employment/schooling combination or work search;
5) provide DNA sample;
6) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
On count 3, disorderly conduct, the defendant is sentenced to the Manitowoc County Jail for one (1) day, time served.
$280.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 11-29-16 or 5 days county jail for failure to pay.
Minutes.
